" ...................... . ..................................................... ... 377 \"ABOUT WHICH NOT MANY PEOPLE ARE KNOWLEDGEABLE.\" ................................................ 385 ''THUS, HE WHO AVOIDS DOUBTFUL MATTERS CLEARS HIMSELF IN REGARD TO HIS RELIGION AND HIS HONOR.\" .................................................................................................................... 387 \"BUT HE WHO FALLS INTO THE DOUBTFUL MATTERS FALLS INTO THAT WHICH IS UNLAWFUL.\" ..... 387 \"LIKE THE SHEPHERD WHO PASTURES AROUND A SANCTUARY, All BUT GRAZING THEREIN. VERILY EVERY KING HAS A SANCTUARY AND ALLAH'S SANCTUARY IS HIS PROHIBITIONS.\" ...................... 388 \"IN THE BODY THERE IS A MORSEL OF FLESH WHICH, IF IT BE SOUND, All THE BODY IS SOUND AND WHICH, IF IT BE DISEASED, All OF IT IS DISEASED. THIS PART OF THE BODY IS THE HEART.\" .......... 390 SIGNS OF THE HEART .......................................... . . ...................... . ..................... ............ 391 OTHER POINTS RELATED TO THIS HADITH ........................................... .............................. 393 SUMMARY OF THE HADITH ............................................................................................ 395 HADITH #7: ''THE RELIGION IS NASEEHAH\" ....•••••••..•••••••••....•••••••••••••.....••••••••...•...•. 397 SELECTED VOCABULARY ..................... ........................................................................... 397 TAKHREEJ ................................................................................................................... 397 GENERAL COMMENTS ABOUT THIS HADITH .................................................................. .... 398 THE NARRATOR: TAMEEM AL-DAARI .................................................................. ............. 398 \"THE RELIGION IS THE NASEEHAH.\" ................................................................................. 398 \"To ALLAH\" ............................................................................................................... 402 \"To HIS BOOK\" ........................ ................................................................................... 403 \"TO HIS MESSENGER\" ............ ...................................................................................... 404 \"TO THE LEADERS OF THE MUSLIMS\" ............................................................................... 405 \"TO THE COMMON FOLK OF THE MUSLIMS\" ...................................................................... 409 THE IMPORTANCE OFAL-NASEEHAH ...... : ......................................................................... 411 IS NASEEHAH ONLY A COMMUNAL OBLIGATION? .............................................................. 412 OTHER POINTS RELATED TO THIS HADITH ......................................................................... 413 SUMMARY OF THE HADITH ...................................................................................... ...... 414 HADITH #8: \"I HAVE BEEN ORDERED TO FIGHT ••• \" •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••.••.• 417 SELECTED VOCABULARY ................................................................................................ 417 TAKHREEJ ................................................................................................................... 418 iv Table of Contents GENERAL COMMENTS ABOUT THE HADITH ....................................................................... 418 DIFFERENT NARRATIONS OF THIS HADITH ............... .......................................................... 418 ABOUT THE NARRATOR ................................................................................................. 419 \"I HAVE BEEN ORDERED\" ............................................................................................... 420 \"TO FIGHT AGAINST THE PEOPLE\" .................................................................................... 420 \"UNTIL THEY TEST